# Overview

This report fits a **Random Forest** regression model to the *Social Media User
Analysis* dataset (Kaggle, 1.5 M synthetic profiles) as a complement to the baseline
Multiple Linear Regression described in the project proposal.  The goal is to predict
two response variables:

| Response Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `self_reported_happiness` | Self-reported happiness score (1–10) |
| `perceived_stress_score` | Perceived stress score (0–40) |

The **primary predictor of interest** is `time_on_explore_per_day` — the minutes per
day spent on Instagram's Explore page — used as a proxy for passive, comparison-driven
browsing ("doom-scrolling").  Demographic and lifestyle variables are included as
confounding controls.

