# Data

## Load Dataset

The full CSV contains ~1.55 M rows.  We draw a stratified random sample of
**50,000 rows** for model training and evaluation — large enough to capture the
population structure while keeping computation tractable.

```{r load-data}
set.seed(472)

DATA_PATH <- "instagram_usage_lifestyle.csv"

NEEDED_COLS <- c(
  "time_on_explore_per_day",
  "daily_active_minutes_instagram",
  "time_on_reels_per_day",
  "time_on_feed_per_day",
  "sessions_per_day",
  "reels_watched_per_day",
  "stories_viewed_per_day",
  "average_session_length_minutes",
  "age", "gender", "income_level", "urban_rural",
  "exercise_hours_per_week", "sleep_hours_per_night",
  "self_reported_happiness", "perceived_stress_score"
)

# data.table::fread reads only the selected columns — ~10x faster than read.csv
dt_full <- fread(DATA_PATH, select = NEEDED_COLS)
cat("Full dataset (selected cols):", nrow(dt_full), "rows x", ncol(dt_full), "cols\n")

# Draw a random sample of 50,000 rows
set.seed(472)
sample_idx <- sample(nrow(dt_full), size = 10000, replace = FALSE)
df_raw     <- as.data.frame(dt_full[sample_idx])

cat("Working sample:          ", nrow(df_raw), "rows (sampled from", nrow(dt_full), "total)\n")
```

## Variable Selection & Cleaning

```{r clean}
FEATURES <- c(
  # ── Primary predictor ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  "time_on_explore_per_day",
  # ── Additional Instagram usage ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  "daily_active_minutes_instagram",
  "time_on_reels_per_day",
  "time_on_feed_per_day",
  "sessions_per_day",
  "reels_watched_per_day",
  "stories_viewed_per_day",
  "average_session_length_minutes",
  # ── Demographic controls ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  "age",
  "gender",
  "income_level",
  "urban_rural",
  # ── Lifestyle controls ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  "exercise_hours_per_week",
  "sleep_hours_per_night"
)

RESPONSES <- c("self_reported_happiness", "perceived_stress_score")

df <- df_raw %>%
  select(all_of(c(FEATURES, RESPONSES))) %>%
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.factor)) %>%
  drop_na()

cat("Modelling dataset:", nrow(df), "rows,", ncol(df), "columns\n")
```

