# Random Forest Models

Two separate Random Forest regression models are trained — one per response variable —
using an **80 / 20 train–test split** and **`ntree = 300`** trees.  The default
`mtry = floor(p/3)` is used for regression forests.

## Train / Test Split

```{r split}
set.seed(472)
n_total   <- nrow(df)
train_idx <- sample(seq_len(n_total), size = floor(0.80 * n_total))

train <- df[ train_idx, ]
test  <- df[-train_idx, ]

cat("Training rows:", nrow(train), " | Test rows:", nrow(test), "\n")
```

## Model 1 — Predicting Happiness Score

```{r rf-happiness}
set.seed(472)

feat_cols <- intersect(FEATURES, colnames(df))

rf_happiness <- randomForest(
  x          = train[, feat_cols],
  y          = train$self_reported_happiness,
  ntree      = 200,
  importance = TRUE
)

print(rf_happiness)
```

### Test-Set Performance

```{r perf-happiness}
pred_happiness <- predict(rf_happiness, newdata = test[, feat_cols])

rmse_h <- sqrt(mean((test$self_reported_happiness - pred_happiness)^2))
mae_h  <- mean(abs(test$self_reported_happiness   - pred_happiness))
ss_res <- sum((test$self_reported_happiness - pred_happiness)^2)
ss_tot <- sum((test$self_reported_happiness - mean(test$self_reported_happiness))^2)
r2_h   <- 1 - ss_res / ss_tot

cat(sprintf("Happiness Model  |  RMSE: %.3f  |  MAE: %.3f  |  R²: %.3f\n",
            rmse_h, mae_h, r2_h))
```

## Model 2 — Predicting Stress Score

```{r rf-stress}
set.seed(472)

rf_stress <- randomForest(
  x          = train[, feat_cols],
  y          = train$perceived_stress_score,
  ntree      = 200,
  importance = TRUE
)

print(rf_stress)
```

### Test-Set Performance

```{r perf-stress}
pred_stress <- predict(rf_stress, newdata = test[, feat_cols])

rmse_s   <- sqrt(mean((test$perceived_stress_score - pred_stress)^2))
mae_s    <- mean(abs(test$perceived_stress_score   - pred_stress))
ss_res_s <- sum((test$perceived_stress_score - pred_stress)^2)
ss_tot_s <- sum((test$perceived_stress_score - mean(test$perceived_stress_score))^2)
r2_s     <- 1 - ss_res_s / ss_tot_s

cat(sprintf("Stress Model     |  RMSE: %.3f  |  MAE: %.3f  |  R²: %.3f\n",
            rmse_s, mae_s, r2_s))
```

