# Variable Importance

**`%IncMSE`** measures the average increase in Mean Squared Error when a variable's
values are randomly permuted across out-of-bag samples.  A larger value indicates
greater importance to predictive accuracy.

## Happiness Model

```{r imp-happiness, fig.height=5}
imp_h <- importance(rf_happiness, type = 1) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("Variable") %>%
  rename(IncMSE = `%IncMSE`) %>%
  arrange(desc(IncMSE))

ggplot(imp_h, aes(x = reorder(Variable, IncMSE), y = IncMSE, fill = IncMSE)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.7) +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "#90CAF9", high = "#0D47A1") +
  labs(title = "Variable Importance — Happiness Score",
       subtitle = "Metric: % Increase in MSE when variable is permuted (OOB)",
       x = NULL, y = "% Increase in MSE") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
```

## Stress Model

```{r imp-stress, fig.height=5}
